From: Freebuff-Termux maintainer
Date: Tue May 26 2026
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Add android-arm64 platform mapping

On Termux, process.platform returns "android". The PLATFORM_TARGETS
map in index.js doesn't have an android entry, causing the download
to fail with "Unsupported platform".

This patch maps android-arm64 to the linux-arm64 binary, since they
are the same architecture and the binary works with glibc on Termux.

diff --git a/index.js b/index.js
index b47a3a2..c8e1f4f 100644
--- a/index.js
+++ b/index.js
@@ -12,6 +12,7 @@ const PLATFORM_TARGETS = {
   'darwin-x64': `${packageName}-darwin-x64.tar.gz`,
   'darwin-arm64': `${packageName}-darwin-arm64.tar.gz`,
   'win32-x64': `${packageName}-win32-x64.tar.gz`,
+  'android-arm64': `${packageName}-linux-arm64.tar.gz`,  // Termux
 };
